#import "../../lib.typ": chapter

#chapter(19, "A recollection of hope")[
  It was currently 7 PM in the Narumi household.

  Receiving the message that her parents would not make it in time for dinner,
  Mona had no choice other than to cook dinner for her and her sister again.
  Honestly, having to cook like this for three days straight is totally
  something out of the ordinary, especially considering that her father was
  always arriving home on time.

  When she entered the kitcheen, she caught her sister wearing an apron while
  happily saying "Let me help!". Of course, Mona could see nothing except
  impure thoughts within those eyes, and as a result, Sena would be kicked out
  of the kitchen entirely. After a bit of moping, Sena had no other choice other
  than sitting at the dining table and waiting for her sister to finish cooking.

  After a twenty-minute cooking session, everything was ready. Since it was a
  meal for just the two of them, there was nothing that fancy: just some boiled
  eggs and some stir-fried meat. And rice too, of course.

  Mona settled on the opposite side to the seat Sena was sitting at, while
  purposefully putting her schoolbag on the empty seat next to her. However, her
  attempts were futile, as her sister would instantly jumped to that seat after
  tugging that bag of hers away.

  "This is revenge for that morning, Mona!"

  After the torture session of her sister, both physically and mentally, Mona
  could finally have dinner in peace.

  "So you went on a karaoke session with friends today? How rare!"

  "It's not that big of a deal, sis." Mona replied nonchalantly, as she grabbed
  another piece of meat with her chopsticks.

  "The last day you also said you made friends, too!" Sena happily cheered,
  "Their names were Uto and Mikota, right?"

  "It's Uta and Mikoto!"

  "Oh right! No wonder why it was so hard to say their names."

  Mona, tired of her sister, returned her focus back to the meal. Even though
  the food was pretty bland today, it was still something she had not eaten for
  a long time. That alone made the food much better for her.

  Meanwhile, Sena did not like this meal a bit, but she was not in any position
  to complain. If she had cooked, not letting the kitchen on fire alone would be
  a miracle.

  So like any spoiled kid who could not finish their meals properly, Sena
  focused her attention to her smartphone.

  "Hmm, I've been looking at Mikoto-chan's Mitter replies... And she's been
  commenting quite regularly!"

  "I don't think a fashion model should go and stalk their fans..."

  "She's your friend, right? I wanted to make sure you're in good hands."

  "Who do you think she is? My mom?" Mona replied, "Also, don't you know that
  social media is where the fakest persona of people are displayed?"

  "I mean yeah..., but she's been commenting for a pretty long time, y'know."
  Sena scrolled through the replies section on the account alledgely belonged to
  Mikoto, "See, at least she's been doing this for five months, and this shows
  no signs of ending."

  Mona took a quick glance. _"Damn, every comment of her is different, she's
  really hardcore, huh?"_

  "So, what do you think of her, then?"

  "Well- I think she's a pretty good person, I guess!"

  "What a generic remark." Mona put the final piece of rice into her mouth,
  before getting more rice from the rice cooker.

  "Okay, so Mikoto-chan is okay, I think it's time to see how Uta-chan really
  is."

  "You are not stopping, huh?"

  "Let me see who is following Mikoto-chan..." Sena clicked on the "14
  following" button, trying to find Uta's profile.

  After a while of searching, she ended off with no potential candidates.

  "There's no one named Uta here..."

  "Well, Uta is pretty well-versed with this, so I don't think she would dox her
  real name on Mitter." Mona remarked.

  "Mona... do you have any social media of her?" Sena asked in despair.

  "I'm not a stalker like you, so no." Mona said with a mischievous tone, "Also,
  sis, if you don't eat, it will get cold, y'know."

  "Wait, Mona. Did you, perchance, have her on Mine?"

  "Yes, so what?"

  "Give me your phone NOW." Sena snatched the phone that was lying on the dining
  table. After unlocking it with the exact passcode Mona just changed one week
  earlier, she tapped on the Mine icon on Mona's homescreen.

  "Wait! How did you know the passcode?" Mona angrily questioned.

  // meta witch reference btw
  "A secret!" Sena pressed her finger on her mouth in a mischievous manner.
]
